==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Measurement
<hw>Meas"ure*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act or result of measuring; mensuration; <as>as, <ex>measurement</ex> is
required</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The extent, size, capacity, amount. or quantity
ascertained by measuring; <as>as, its <ex>measurement</ex> is five
acres</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Measurer</ent>⟦br⟧
